This paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence in decision-making, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses how rational decision-making can lead to a more efficient marketplace, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computational economics (cs.EC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence in optimizing choices, which falls under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
